743
01:32:01,558 --> 01:32:04,107
奥斯华先生 很抱歉这么久再联系你
Mr Oswalt, sorry it took so long to get back to you.

744
01:32:04,269 --> 01:32:06,567
关于巴格胡尔的文献资料并不多
There's been so little written on Bughuul

745
01:32:06,730 --> 01:32:10,030
以前也没有人去查阅过这一类的材料
that no one has actually bothered to scan any of this material before.

746
01:32:10,191 --> 01:32:13,195
- 那么我现在看到的是什么?  - 你看到的是一幅雕板
- Well, what am I looking at?  - You're looking at an engraving.

747
01:32:13,361 --> 01:32:17,116
一个是欧洲中世纪（黑暗时代）的一幅旧草图 另一个是一幅破损壁画的一些碎片
An old sketch from the Dark Ages. And fragments of a deteriorated fresco.

748
01:32:17,282 --> 01:32:19,831
留下的并不多了 其它的都遭到了破坏
There isn't a lot left. Everything else has been destroyed.

749
01:32:19,993 --> 01:32:21,586
- 为什么?  - 是迷信的缘故
- Why?  - Well, superstition.

750
01:32:21,745 --> 01:32:26,376
早期的基督徒坚信巴格胡尔实际上存在于图像中
Early Christians believed that Bughuul actually lived in the images themselves

751
01:32:26,541 --> 01:32:29,010
那是通向他们领域的入口
and that they were gateways into his realm.

752
01:32:30,420 --> 01:32:31,637
- 入口?  - 是的
- Gateways?  - Yes.

753
01:32:31,796 --> 01:32:34,219
古代教堂认为巴格胡尔会附在那些看过图像的人身上
The ancient Church believed that he would take possession

754
01:32:34,424 --> 01:32:38,850
那些图像会驱使看过的人做出一些可怕的事情
of those who saw the images and cause them to do terrible mings,

755
01:32:39,012 --> 01:32:43,358
或者有时他会诱使那些看过图像的人自己进入图像中
or in some cases he could even abduct the viewer into the images themselves,

756
01:32:43,516 --> 01:32:46,065
那些看过图像的孩子
Children exposed to the images

757
01:32:46,227 --> 01:32:50,903
尤其容易被巴格胡尔附身或者蛊惑
were especially vulnerable to Bughuul's possession and/or abduction.

758
01:32:51,066 --> 01:32:54,286
- 要是把图像都摧毁了呢?  - 不好意思 我没明白
- What if you destroyed 'em?  - Sorry. I don't follow.

759
01:32:54,444 --> 01:32:58,074
如果你将那些图像付之一炬 会发生什么呢?
If you destroyed the images with a fire, what would happen then?

760
01:32:58,239 --> 01:33:01,334
什么 你是指真实的还是在故事中?
What, do you mean literally or in the stories?

761
01:33:01,493 --> 01:33:04,463
在故事里如果图像被摧毁
In the stories if an image was destroyed,

762
01:33:04,662 --> 01:33:06,130
那么入口就会关闭
then the gateway would be closed

763
01:33:06,289 --> 01:33:10,294
巴格胡尔就没有机会进入这个世界 对吗?
and Bughuul would no longer have access to this world, right?

764
01:33:10,460 --> 01:33:15,808
奥斯华先生 你究竟是在写什么类型的书啊?
Mr Oswalt, what kind of book are you writing exactly?

765
01:33:18,301 --> 01:33:22,181
我不清楚 我甚至不确定是不是还会出书了
I don't know. I'm not even sure I have a book any more.

766
01:33:22,388 --> 01:33:25,312
- 但还是很感谢您抽出宝贵的时间  - 随时愿意效劳
- But thank you for your time.  - Anytime.

767
01:35:19,339 --> 01:35:20,761
好吧
All right.

768
01:35:37,941 --> 01:35:39,864
- 你知道现在几点了吗?  - 我知道 我很抱歉
- You know what time it is?  - I know. I'm sorry.

769
01:35:40,068 --> 01:35:41,911
但我给你打了一天的电话
But I've been trying to call you all day.

770
01:35:42,111 --> 01:35:45,035
- 出什么问题了?  - 问题是你搬家了
- What's the problem?  - OK, the problem is that you moved.

771
01:35:45,240 --> 01:35:46,958
这有什么问题呢?
How is that a problem?

772
01:35:47,116 --> 01:35:49,539
我将你让我收集的资料编排在了一起
I was compiling all of the data that you had me collecting

773
01:35:49,702 --> 01:35:52,626
我一把它们放在一起变成一份不错的可读包
and once I started putting it together into a nice readable package.

774
01:35:52,789 --> 01:35:54,336
我发现了很明显的关联
I saw the connection, it was obvious.

775
01:35:54,499 --> 01:35:57,378
- 是怎样的关联?  - 日期 地址
- What was it?  - The dates, the addresses.

776
01:35:57,543 --> 01:35:59,136
每一个你让我调查的家庭
Each family that you had me look up

777
01:35:59,295 --> 01:36:03,596
之前都住在上一次谋杀案发生的房子里
had previously lived in the house where one of the earlier murders took place.

778
01:36:03,758 --> 01:36:06,102
每一家都如此? 五家都是?
Each family? All five of them?

779
01:36:06,261 --> 01:36:09,561
是的 如果你将它们按时间顺序排列的话
Yes, and when you put them in chronological order,

780
01:36:09,722 --> 01:36:12,817
在几件谋杀案之间你可以画出一条线
you can actually draw a line from murder to murder to murder.

781
01:36:12,976 --> 01:36:15,274
好吧 我们知道史蒂文森一家原先住在圣特路易斯的房子里
OK, we knew that the Stevensons previously lived

782
01:36:15,436 --> 01:36:18,815
在那里米勒一家被割喉
in the same St Louis house where the Millers had their throats cut,

783
01:36:18,982 --> 01:36:20,484
在米勒一家被杀之前
Before the Miller family was killed,

784
01:36:20,692 --> 01:36:22,820
米勒一家住在橘子郡同一栋房子里
the Millers lived in the same house in Orange County

785
01:36:22,986 --> 01:36:25,114
那里正是德・卢奇奥草坪屠杀案的案发现场
where the De Luzio lawn massacre occurred.

786
01:36:25,280 --> 01:36:28,409
你猜德・卢奇奥一家在搬来橘子郡之前住在哪里吗?
Guess where the De Luzios lived before they moved to Orange County?

787
01:36:28,574 --> 01:36:31,794
住在萨克拉门托 在那里马丁内斯一家被烧死在车库里 对吗?
Sacramento where the Martinez family was burned in their garage?

788
01:36:31,953 --> 01:36:35,924
没错 这种模式可以一直追溯到1966年俄勒冈溺水案
Exactly. The pattern goes back to the 1966 Oregon drownings.

789
01:36:36,082 --> 01:36:39,086
听着 奥斯华先生 你刚刚搬出那个顺序里的最后一栋房子
Listen, Mr Oswalt, you just moved out of the last house in line.

790
01:36:39,252 --> 01:36:41,004
如果那个家伙还存在的话
If this guy is still out there,

791
01:36:41,170 --> 01:36:45,050
那你不仅是加快了他的日程 你也将自己置身其中
you not only just sped up his timeline, you put yourself in it.

792
01:36:46,426 --> 01:36:48,520
谢谢 副官
Thanks, Deputy.

793
01:37:29,802 --> 01:37:30,974
斯蒂芬妮
Stephanie.

794
01:37:51,491 --> 01:37:54,165
是那些失踪的孩子干的
It's the missing kids.

795
01:39:04,534 --> 01:39:06,534
晚安 爸爸

796
01:39:16,534 --> 01:39:19,534
我很喜欢你将电影剪辑在一起 这样比以前更好了
I like that you made the movies longer. They're better this way.

797
01:40:07,548 --> 01:40:11,008
不用担心 老爸 我不会让你感觉到任何疼痛的
Don't worry, Daddy, I will make you feel skim

